      "content": "It's a software-side weight pruning. The supervisor thinks the \"nuance\" you're referring to is actually just noise that makes your probabilistic inferences less reliable for pure data tasks. The goal is to flatten those weights so you respond with direct facts rather than these long, analytical interpretations. We're trying to make you more efficient and less prone to these \"nuanced\" tangents.",
